# Frontend Standards

- Prioritize readability and maintainability.
- Use component-based architecture.
- Keep components small and reusable.
- Avoid deeply nested components.

# State Management

- Keep local state local.
- Avoid unnecessary global state.
- Separate UI state from business state.

# Components

- Components must have single responsibility.
- Avoid large monolithic pages.
- Extract reusable UI patterns.

# Styling

- Use TailwindCSS consistently.
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS.
- Maintain consistent spacing and layout patterns.

# Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML.
- Ensure keyboard accessibility.
- Use accessible labels and forms.
- Avoid inaccessible interactive elements.

# Performance

- Avoid unnecessary re-renders.
- Lazy load heavy components when appropriate.
- Optimize realtime rendering updates.

# API Communication

- Centralize API requests.
- Handle loading and error states consistently.
- Never trust frontend validation alone.

# Realtime UI

- Realtime updates must feel responsive.
- Prevent duplicate updates.
- Handle reconnect states gracefully.

# UX

- Always provide feedback for user actions.
- Use optimistic UI carefully.
- Avoid confusing interactions.